			<title>Peaceweek in Greece</title>
			<link>http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/index.php/nieuws-140/kamp-van-de-maand-mainmenu-120/286-pw-greece</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/index.php/nieuws-140/kamp-van-de-maand-mainmenu-120/286-pw-greece</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<div class="feed-description"><p><img src="http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/via-media/logo%20cbw.png" border="0" width="300" /></p>
<p> </p>
<p>The Peace Week in Athens is one of 8 Peace Weeks organized in framework of ‘Citizens Beyond Walls’ project, which focuses on rise of extreme rise movements and parties in Europe. The aim of the project is raising awareness of Athenian society on issues of multicultural diversity, nationality and inclusion.</p>
<p><span>The study theme will be focused on the issues of peace and diversity. It will also approach the subject of Citizens Beyond Walls, through an overview of the research going on in Greece about the extreme-right movements and how to counteract their influence on society.</span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;"> </span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">For more info visit: </span></p>
<p><a href="http://citizensbeyondwalls.org/peace-weeks/">http://citizensbeyondwalls.org/peace-weeks/</a></p></div>]]></description>
