			<title>Join the first PEACE WEEK in Sofia</title>
			<link>http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/index.php/nieuws-140/kamp-van-de-maand-mainmenu-120/284-peaceweek-bulgaria</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/index.php/nieuws-140/kamp-van-de-maand-mainmenu-120/284-peaceweek-bulgaria</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<div class="feed-description"><p><span>The Peace Week in Sofia is one of eight Peace Weeks organized within the framework of 'Citizens Beyond Walls' project, which focuses on rise of extreme right wing movements and parties in Europe. The aim of the project is raising awareness in Bulgarian society on issues of diversity, nationality and inclusion. Because the extreme right wing parties in Bulgaria seem particularly interested in refugees and asylum-seekers, this topic will be addressed specifically during this peace week. The peace week will be organized by CVS-Bulgaria.</span></p>
<p><span><img src="http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/via-media/content/newsletter/logo%20CBW.png" border="0" width="250" /></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Don't miss your chance! Apply for one of the Peace Weeks now! </span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Most of the costs are covered, you only need to pay 45% of your travel (up to 200 euros) and the regular application fee. </span><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Questions? You can always reach us at </span><a href="mailto:info@stichtingvia.nl" style="line-height: 1.3em;">info@stichtingvia.nl</a></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Don't wait as the number of places is limited! </span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.3em;"> </span></p></div>]]></description>
