		<item>
			<title>Join one “Non-violence needs Nature” project!</title>
			<link>http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/index.php/nieuws-140/kamp-van-de-maand-mainmenu-120/276-non-violence-needs-nature</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/index.php/nieuws-140/kamp-van-de-maand-mainmenu-120/276-non-violence-needs-nature</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<div class="feed-description"><p><img src="http://www.via.dds.nl/joomla2/via-media/content/camp-of-the-week/7547.jpg" border="0" alt="" /></p>
<p>This week want to bring you closer one of the “Non-violence needs Nature” projects, called Living permaculture, which takes place in Suderbyn ekoby (<a href="http://www.suderbyn.se">www.suderbyn.se</a>) which is located on the island Gotland. Suderbyn is a young community founded in 2008 and based on ecological and sustainable lifestyle.<span style="color: #135cae; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3em;"><br /></span></p>
<p><span>The practical work will be directly linked to the daily life of the Suderbyns community: participants will help in small projects using sustainable materials and learn about sustainable building and house maintenance. They will also work in the community garden and learn about organic farming methods and sustainable food production.</span></p>
<p><span><span>This workcamp will provide direct experience and knowledge about sustainability, alternated to study sessions and other ways of informal learning related to the connection between North and South of the World, human rights and social inclusion.</span></span></p>
<p><span><span>Check out all the info here <a href="http://workcamps.info/icamps/NL-VIA/nl/camp-details/camp-7547.html">http://workcamps.info/icamps/NL-VIA/nl/camp-details/camp-7547.html</a></span></span></p></div>]]></description>
